time_quotations.quote: Time is what we want most, but what we use worst.
time_quotations.author: William Penn

time_quotations.quote: The two most powerful warriors are patience and time.
time_quotations.author: Leo Tolstoy

time_quotations.quote: Time flies over us, but leaves its shadow behind.
time_quotations.author: Nathaniel Hawthorne

time_quotations.quote: Time is a created thing. To say 'I don't have time,' is like saying, 'I don't want to.
time_quotations.author: Lao Tzu

time_quotations.quote: Time is an equal opportunity employer. Each human being has exactly the same number of hours and minutes every day.
time_quotations.author: Denis Waitley

time_quotations.quote: Time is a file that wears and makes no noise.
time_quotations.author: Isaac Watts

time_quotations.quote: Time is a sort of river of passing events, and strong is its current; no sooner is a thing brought to sight than it is swept by and another takes its place, and this too will be swept away.
time_quotations.author: Marcus Aurelius

time_quotations.quote: Lost time is never found again.
time_quotations.author: Benjamin Franklin

time_quotations.quote: Time and tide wait for no man.
time_quotations.author: Geoffrey Chaucer

time_quotations.quote: Time is the most valuable thing a man can spend.
time_quotations.author: Theophrastus
